15. Typographic quotes: Russian «» → US \u201c \u201d (“ ”) for ALL display text quoting (record names, process names, element names, form names — not just templates). Straight quotes " reserved for JSON syntax only.
16. HTML tags preserved in Content — translate inner text only. Inline styles, links, attributes intact.
17. BPMN token values are compound mixed RU/EN strings — require sub-string TM matching. Remaining ~3,031 pending values bottleneck.
18. Trigger/process descriptions may contain technical alias references in angle brackets or quoted attribute/template references (for example `<Obrabotkasobytiya>`, `<Vypolnenieraboty>`, `attribute “Obkhod”`). Keep those alias tokens exactly as-is until the actual aliases are renamed. Store the intended future alias/display mapping in TM only when that alias-rename work is performed; do not localize alias references inside trigger text ahead of the alias change.
