## Translation Quality Rule — WHOLE SENTENCES ONLY
- **ABSOLUTE RULE:** Localization operates on **complete sentences/phrases**, never word-level fragments
- **NO word soup:** Do not replace individual words inside longer strings — this creates garbage (e.g., `Ср→Sr` in `Средний→Srедний`)
- **TM lookup may use stems/fuzzy** for candidate matching, but output must be **complete sentence translation**
- **If TM lacks a full match**, the ENTIRE newValue string must be translated as one unit, not token-by-token substitution
- **Mid-word corruption prevention:** Any replacement shorter than a full word boundary is forbidden. `(?<!\w)...(?!\w)` regex is the ONLY safe way to handle sub-word tokens
- **Star ratings (⭐) are visual indicators, never translated:** Keep star emoji sequences identical in both `Ru` and `En` fields of LocalizedTextModel. Never replace stars with text (e.g., ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ → Excellent). Stars are quality indicators in the UI, not linguistic content.
- **LocalizedTextModel rule:** Both `Ru` and `En` fields get the same English text. For star ratings, both get the same star sequence. No Cyrillic left in either field, ever.

